<p>Here is the idea:</p>

<p><a href="https://protesilaos.com/assets/images/attachments/2023-03-31-denote-menu.png"><img alt="Sample of Denote menu in Emacs" src="https://protesilaos.com/assets/images/attachments/2023-03-31-denote-menu.png" /></a></p>

<p>[ The exact style of the menu is controlled by the toolkit, not the
  active theme. ]</p>

<p>Specific entries are available only in the right context, such as to
toggle the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">denote-dired-mode</code> when in Dired buffers or to show
backlinks when in a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">text-mode</code> buffer (or its derivatives, like
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">org-mode</code>).</p>

<p>The menu enhances the accessibility of Denote by making its commands
easier to discover.</p>

<p>Note that this is a development snapshot.  I may still tweak things
and also cover the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">context-menu-mode</code>, though the intent is clear.</p>

<p><strong>UPDATE 2023-03-31 19:51 +0300</strong>.  I added support for
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">context-menu-mode</code>.  Also made lots of other tweaks.</p>

